summary:
The Security Council,
Having considered the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force, 
1. Calls upon the parties concerned to implement immediately its resolution 338 (1973) of 22 October 1973;
2. Welcomes efforts by the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force to implement the Secretary-General's zero tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, requests the Secretary-General to continue taking necessary action and keep the Security Council informed, and urges troop-contributing countries to investigate and punish such acts involving their personnel;
3. Decides to renew the mandate of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force for six months, until 30 June 2006;
4. Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338 (1973) at the end of this period.
